In this spiral the odd squares (1, 9, 25, 49, …) always sit in the bottom-right corner of the successive squares

bottom-right of layer n   →   number (2n+1)² at the coordinate (n, –n).

1. Locate 2026  
45² = 2025 < 2026 < 47² = 2209  
Hence 2025 is the bottom-right corner of the square whose half-side is 22 (n = 22),
so it is at (22, –22).
The next number, 2026, is one step to the right, i.e. at (23, –22).

2. Coordinates of the eight neighbours of (23, –22)

          y+1        (22,-21) (23,-21) (24,-21)
          y          (22,-22)  2026     (24,-22)
          y–1        (22,-23) (23,-23) (24,-23)

3. Value at a given coordinate (x, y)   
Let n = max(|x|, |y|);  M = (2n+1)² (the number at (n, –n)).
Going anticlockwise round the edge:

bottom:  y = –n,  d = n – x  
left:    x = –n,  d = 2n + (y + n)  
top:     y =  n,  d = 4n + (x + n)  
right:   x =  n,  d = 6n + (n – y)

Number = M – d.

4. Evaluate every neighbour

(22,-23)  n=23 ➜ M=2209,  d=1            → 2208  
(23,-23)  n=23 ➜ M=2209,  d=0            → 2209  
(24,-23)  n=24 ➜ M=2401,  d=191          → 2210  
(22,-22)  n=22 ➜ M=2025,  d=0            → 2025  
(24,-22)  n=24 ➜ M=2401,  d=190          → 2211  
(22,-21)  n=22 ➜ M=2025,  d=175          → 1850  
(23,-21)  n=23 ➜ M=2209,  d=182          → 2027  
(24,-21)  n=24 ➜ M=2401,  d=189          → 2212  

5. Sum of the eight numbers  
1850 + 2025 + 2027 + 2208 + 2209 + 2210 + 2211 + 2212 = 16 952

Answer: 16952
